%2Fi.insider.com%2F671be6eca0a0cc14f2242011%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20report%20shows%20Reddit%20is%20making%20money%20fast%20from%20advertising%20revenue.%3Cp%3ESpencer%20Platt%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EReddit's%20ad%20revenue%20is%20growing%20faster%20than%20any%20other%20social%20media%20platform%2C%20according%20to%20EMARKETER.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20report%20says%20Reddit's%20user%20base%20is%20expanding%20due%20to%20its%20unique%20%26quot%3Bsocial%26quot%3B%20feel.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStill%2C%20advertisers%20face%20challenges%20on%20Reddit%20due%20to%20the%20site's%20unique%20communities.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20report%20shows%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-stock-drops-google-algorithm-tweak-hurt-its-user-growth-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit's%20ad%20revenue%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20growing%20faster%20than%20any%20other%20social%20media%20platform.%20Still%2C%20advertising%20on%20the%20app%20isn't%20as%20easy%20as%20it%20seems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20from%20EMARKETER%20says%20that%20Reddit's%20year-over-year%20ad%20revenue%20will%20grow%20by%20more%20than%2030%25%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20its%20estimates.%20EMARKETER%20is%20a%20digital%20marketing%20research%20company%20owned%20by%20Business%20Insider%20parent%20company%2C%20Axel%20Springer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20highest%20ad%20revenue%20growth%20among%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-mainstream-google-traffic-stock-revenue-human-users-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%20platforms%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20Reddit%20came%20from%20TikTok%20with%2025%25%20and%20Instagram%20with%2015%25%20year-over-year%20growth%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-comments-ai-training-models-google-openai-jen-wong-huffman-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECEO%20Steve%20Huffman%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20said%20that%20Reddit%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20places%20left%20on%20the%20internet%20that%20allows%20people%20to%20hold%20communal%20conversations%20with%20each%20other.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-ceo-platform-arms-race-ai-training-steve-huffman-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHuffman%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20event%20in%20October%20that%20Reddit%20posts%20are%20valuable%20for%20search%20engines%20and%20AI%20because%20they%20contain%20a%20wealth%20of%20%26quot%3Bcolloquial%20words%20about%20pretty%20much%20every%20topic%26quot%3B%20that%20are%20constantly%20updated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20from%20EMARKETER%20said%20in%20the%20report%20that%20Reddit's%20user%20base%20is%20growing%2C%20partly%20because%20it%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20social%20media%20platforms%20that%20still%20feels%20%26quot%3Bsocial.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20big%20reason%20why%20it's%20one%20of%20the%20only%20social%20platforms%20seeing%20time%20spent%20gains%20in%202025%2C%20per%20our%20forecasts%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20while%20the%20social%20feel%20of%20Reddit%20is%20attracting%20swaths%20of%20new%20users%2C%20it%20could%20make%20it%20hard%20for%20advertisers%20to%20come%20across%20as%20relatable%20on%20the%20site.%20The%20report%20notes%20that%20Reddit%20users%20%26quot%3Btypically%20don't%20want%20brands%20in%20their%20conversations%2C%20especially%20ones%20that%20aren't%20upfront%20about%20who%20they%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20advertisers%20have%20found%20ways%20to%20integrate%20into%20Reddit%20communities%2C%20including%20by%20creating%20employee%20accounts.%20User%20KiethFromSonos%2C%20a%20Sonos%20employee%20who%20asked%20to%20join%20the%20Reddit%20community%20r%2FSonos%2C%20gradually%20earned%20a%20place%20in%20the%20community%2C%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20is%20also%20giving%20advertisers%20tools%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20them%20to%20have%20an%20organic%20presence%20on%20the%20website%2C%20the%20report%20says.%20In%20March%20of%20last%20year%20the%20company%20created%20Reddit%20Pro%2C%20a%20platform%20that%20gives%20advertisers%20analytics%2C%20insights%2C%20and%20publishing%20tools%2C%20and%20earlier%20this%20year%20Reddit%20announced%20a%20new%20format%20that%20lets%20advertisers%20promote%20upcoming%20AMAs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20reached%20for%20comment%20on%20Friday%2C%20a%20Reddit%20spokesperson%20directed%20Business%20Insider%20to%20the%20company's%20quarter%20four%20earnings%20report.%20Reddit%20COO%20Jen%20Wong%20said%20in%20an%20earnings%20call%20on%20February%2012%20that%20the%20company%20saw%20%26quot%3Bbroad%20growth%26quot%3B%20across%20advertising%20verticals%2C%20with%2010%20of%20its%2015%20verticals%20growing%20by%20over%2050%25%20year-over-year.%20Wong%20said%20the%20areas%20that%20saw%20the%20most%20growth%20were%20finance%2C%20retail%2C%20auto%2C%20pharma%2C%20gaming%2C%20and%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20continue%20to%20focus%20on%3A%20one%2C%20driving%20performance%20of%20our%20ad%20solutions%20across%20objectives%3B%20two%2C%20improving%20usability%20for%20our%20advertisers%20and%20productivity%20for%20our%20sales%20force%3B%20and%20three%2C%20offering%20our%20advertisers%20Reddit-unique%20solutions%20and%20ad%20formats%2C%26quot%3B%20Wong%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fs203.q4cdn.com%2F380862485%2Ffiles%2Fdoc_financials%2F2024%2Fq4%2FReddit-Q4-24-Earnings-Call-Transcript.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20call%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-ad-revenue-grows-fastest-among-social-media-platforms-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A174139209