nik%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDaylight-saving%20time%20(DST)%20begins%20this%20Sunday%2C%20March%209%2C%20when%20clocks%20spring%20from%201%3A59%20a.m.%20to%203%20a.m.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20December%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20said%20he%20planned%20to%20end%20DST%20because%20it%20is%20inconvenient%20and%20costly.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20Republican%20colleagues%20and%20golf%20lobbyists%20want%20the%20opposite.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20delicately%20extricating%20himself%20from%20the%20fierce%20and%20contradictory%20political%20drama%20over%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaylight-savings-time-dst-death-heart-attacks-accident%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edaylight-saving%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202024%2C%20Trump%20said%20on%20Truth%20Social%20that%20he%20would%20end%20daylight-saving%20time%20and%20make%20standard%20time%20permanent%20because%20DST%20is%20%26quot%3Binconvenient%20and%20very%20costly%20for%20our%20Nation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20US%20would%20%3Cem%3Estop%3C%2Fem%3E%20winding%20the%20clocks%20forward%20in%20March%2C%20which%20gives%20us%20more%20sunlight%20in%20the%20summer%20nights.%20(This%20year%2C%20clocks%20spring%20forward%20on%20March%209.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20president%20would%20have%20had%20the%20backing%20of%20health%20experts%20and%20economists.%20Research%20shows%20that%20daylight-saving%20time%20is%20linked%20to%20myriad%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DTgz7p3_5BeI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealth%20problems%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20premature%20and%20accidental%20death%2C%20and%20has%20increased%20energy%20bills%20in%20some%20states.%20Hawaii%20and%20Arizona%20ditched%20DST%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20many%20states%20are%20considering%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%20many%20of%20Trump's%20Republican%20colleagues%20want%20the%20exact%20opposite.%20In%20January%2C%20Florida%20Sen.%20Rick%20Scott%20reignited%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rubio.senate.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F_cache%2Ffiles%2Ffe0d7211-57e1-4b89-90dd-0789768e41dc%2F1055A4494B96C496B17D26F68F852E1C.sunshine-protection-act-of-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESunshine%20Protection%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20make%20DST%20permanent.%20The%20bipartisan%20bill%2C%20first%20introduced%20by%20fellow%20Florida%20Sen.%20Marco%20Rubio%2C%20was%20passed%20unanimously%20by%20the%20Senate%20in%202022%20but%20faltered%20in%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERubio%20and%20Scott%20have%20the%20backing%20of%20golf%20industry%20lobbyists%20who%20say%20afternoon%20golf%20leagues%20rely%20on%20evening%20sun%20and%20generate%20eye-watering%20sums%20of%20money%20for%20their%20sport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReader%2C%20the%20more%20we%20learn%20about%20DST%2C%20the%20more%20convoluted%20it%20seems%20to%20become.%20Trump%20has%20signaled%20that%20he's%20leaving%20this%20squabble%2C%20at%20least%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%2050%2F50%20issue%2C%20and%20if%20something%20is%20a%2050%2F50%20issue%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20get%20excited%20about%20it.%20I%20assume%20people%20would%20like%20to%20have%20more%20light%20later%2C%20but%20some%20people%20would%20like%20to%20have%20more%20light%20earlier%20because%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20take%20their%20kids%20to%20school%20in%20the%20dark%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20told%20reporters%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%20Thursday.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20I%20can%20do%2C%20but%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20like%20it%20one%20way.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20like%20it%20the%20other%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20cheat%20sheet%20on%20why%20the%20DST%20drama%20is%20not%20so%20straightforward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22427858d3-9caa-4760-90c0-a6bd20c3c723%5C%22%3EMany%20states%20have%20an%20opinion%20on%20daylight-savings%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20going%20on%20at%20the%20state%20level%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncsl.org%2Ftransportation%2Fdaylight-saving-time-state-legislation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Conference%20of%20State%20Legislatures%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EHawaii%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20and%20%3Cstrong%3EArizona%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20have%20permanent%20standard%20time.%20That%20means%20their%20clocks%20do%20not%20spring%20forward%20to%20create%20more%20evening%20sunlight.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAt%20least%2019%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20states%20have%20introduced%20bills%20to%20keep%20daylight-saving%20time%20year-round%20(to%20have%20more%20light%20in%20the%20evenings).%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAt%20least%2030%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20states%20have%20bills%20proposing%20permanent%20standard%20time%20(meaning%20more%20light%20in%20the%20mornings).%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20states%20have%20bills%20for%20both.%20Many%20states%20have%20legislation%20that%20says%20they%20will%20follow%20their%20neighboring%20states'%20lead%3B%20if%20they%20switch%20to%20permanent%20DST%20%3Cem%3Eor%3C%2Fem%3E%20permanent%20standard%20time%2C%20they%20will%20follow%20suit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20the%202018%20midterms%2C%20%3Cstrong%3ECalifornia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0voters%20voted%20to%20make%20daylight%20savings%20time%20permanent.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fballotpedia.org%2FCalifornia_Proposition_7%2C_Legislative_Power_to_Change_Daylight_Saving_Time_Measure_(2018)%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThat%20measure%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0got%20stuck%20in%20committee%20meetings.%20In%202024%2C%20CA%20lawmakers%20introduced%20legislation%20proposing%20an%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eend%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20DST%20and%20switching%20to%20permanent%20standard%20time.%20Now%2C%20they're%20in%20a%20stalemate.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2206977741-dea5-40fb-a83e-43b79102eb5c%5C%22%3EHere's%20what's%20happening%20at%20the%20national%20level%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.masslive.com%2Fnews%2Findex.ssf%2F2018%2F10%2Fdaylight_savings_time_2018_when_do_we_turn_back_the_clocks.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECongress%3C%2Fa%3E%20must%20approve%20the%20switch%20to%20permanent%20DST%2C%20but%20states%20do%20not%20need%20federal%20approval%20to%20switch%20to%20permanent%20standard%20time.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20Rick%20Scott%20revived%20the%20bipartisan%20push%20to%20%26quot%3Bstop%20the%20clock%26quot%3B%20and%20make%20DST%20permanent%20through%20the%20Sunshine%20Protection%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Trump%20was%20suggesting%20the%20opposite%2C%20Scott%20issued%20a%20statement%20saying%20he%20expected%20the%20president's%20support.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20excited%20to%20have%20President%20Trump%20back%20in%20the%20White%20House%20and%20fully%20on%20board%20to%20LOCK%20THE%20CLOCK%20so%20we%20can%20get%20this%20good%20bill%20passed%20and%20make%20this%20common-sense%20change%20that%20will%20simplify%20and%20benefit%20the%20lives%20of%20American%20families%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2295f4b2d7-806c-42e3-a51f-f4428f6043a0%5C%22%3EIs%20DST%20good%20or%20bad%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20an%20argument%20for%20daylight-saving%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EGolfing%20hours%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20golf%20industry%20is%20lobbying%20%3Cem%3Ehard%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20DST.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fdaylight-saving-time-golf-e2d2d69f909b1839ced3a8dbd203e521%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Associated%20Press%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%20golf%20executives%20played%20a%20role%20in%20inventing%20DST%2C%20and%20are%20behind%20many%20of%20the%20pro-DST%20bills%20peppered%20across%20US%20legislatures.%20One%20Nebraska%20golf%20course%20manager%20told%20the%20AP%20that%20ending%20daylight%20savings%20would%20cost%20him%20%24500%2C000%20by%20curtailing%20evening%20golf%20clubs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EReduce%20crime%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjenniferdoleac.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F03%2FDoleac_Sanders_DST.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2015%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20crime%20rates%20may%20dip%20with%20more%20evening%20sunlight.%20Further%20research%20is%20needed%20to%20show%20a%20strong%20connection%20between%20crime%20rates%20and%20DST.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20there's%20also%20an%20argument%20against%20daylight-saving%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20costly%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDaylight-saving%20time%20was%20devised%20in%20Germany%20as%20a%20measure%20to%20conserve%20energy%20during%20World%20War%201.%20Now%20we%20know%20it%20doesn't%20really%20work%20that%20way%20%E2%80%94%20a%20study%20found%20that%20people%20in%20Indiana%2C%20for%20example%2C%20spent%20%247%20million%20more%20annually%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-daylight-saving-time-is-bad-2018-3%23dst-may-actually-end-up-costing-us-energy-and-money-instead-of-saving-it-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenergy%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20state%20switched%20to%20DST%20in%202006.%20Employees%20were%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaylight-savings-negative-effects-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20productive%20in%20DST%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20study%20suggested.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20bad%20for%20our%20health%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOverwhelmingly%2C%20research%20shows%20DST%20to%20be%20linked%20to%20poor%20health%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20switch%20itself%20is%20particularly%20harmful%20%E2%80%94%20throwing%20off%20our%20sleep%20cycle%20and%20affecting%20our%20metabolism%2C%20hormones%2C%20and%20inflammation%20control.%20The%20Monday%20after%20DST%20kicks%20in%20is%20associated%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fope